The following sheel session log demonstrated the use of the program ./offset showing what happens when we attempt to read bytes from a file hole:

$ touch tfile // create new empty file
$ ./offset tfile s100000 wabc // seek to offset 100,000, write 'abc'
s100000: seek succeeded
wabc: wrote 3 bytes
$ ls -l tfile
-rw-r--r-- 1 mtk users 100003 <date> <time> tfile
$ ./offset tfile s10000 R5 // seek to offset 10000, read 5 bytes from the hole
s10000: seek succeeded
R5: 00 00 00 00 00 // bytes in hold contain 0